Note:
Runa Standard Library: Blockchain Smart Contract Interface Module

Provides comprehensive Application Binary Interface (ABI) specification and contract
interaction capabilities for blockchain smart contracts. Implements enterprise-grade
ABI encoding/decoding, function signatures, event definitions, and cross-contract
communication. Competitive with production ABI implementations in Ethereum, Solana,
and other leading smart contract platforms.

Features:
- Complete ABI specification with type definitions and function signatures
- ABI encoding and decoding for all standard types
- Function selector calculation and method dispatch
- Event definition and log parsing capabilities
- Contract metadata and documentation integration
- Cross-contract call interfaces and proxy patterns
- Dynamic contract interaction and reflection
- Type safety and validation for contract calls
- Gas estimation for contract function calls
- Contract upgrade and versioning support
- Interface inheritance and composition
- Standard contract interfaces (ERC-20, ERC-721, etc.)
- Contract factory patterns and deployment
- Error handling and custom exception types
- Multi-language binding generation
:End Note

Note: Core ABI Types
Type called "ContractABI":
    contract_name as String
    contract_version as String
    functions as List[FunctionABI]
    events as List[EventABI]
    errors as List[ErrorABI]
    constructor as ConstructorABI
    receive_function as ReceiveFunctionABI
    fallback_function as FallbackFunctionABI
    state_variables as List[StateVariableABI]
    inheritance as List[String]
    metadata as ContractMetadata

Type called "FunctionABI":
    name as String
    function_type as FunctionType
    inputs as List[Parameter]
    outputs as List[Parameter]
    state_mutability as StateMutability
    payable as Boolean
    constant as Boolean
    pure as Boolean
    view as Boolean
    visibility as Visibility
    modifiers as List[String]
    gas_estimate as Integer
    selector as String
    signature as String

Type FunctionType is:
    | FUNCTION
    | CONSTRUCTOR
    | RECEIVE
    | FALLBACK

Type StateMutability is:
    | PURE
    | VIEW
    | NONPAYABLE
    | PAYABLE

Type Visibility is:
    | PUBLIC
    | EXTERNAL
    | INTERNAL
    | PRIVATE

Type called "Parameter":
    name as String
    type as ABIType
    indexed as Boolean
    internal_type as String
    components as List[Parameter]

Type called "ABIType":
    type_name as String
    base_type as BaseType
    array_size as Integer
    is_array as Boolean
    is_dynamic as Boolean
    size_in_bytes as Integer
    components as List[ABIType]

Type BaseType is:
    | UINT
    | INT
    | ADDRESS
    | BOOL
    | BYTES
    | STRING
    | ARRAY
    | TUPLE
    | MAPPING
    | FUNCTION_TYPE

Type called "EventABI":
    name as String
    inputs as List[Parameter]
    anonymous as Boolean
    signature as String
    topic_hash as String

Type called "ErrorABI":
    name as String
    inputs as List[Parameter]
    selector as String

Type called "ConstructorABI":
    inputs as List[Parameter]
    payable as Boolean
    state_mutability as StateMutability

Type called "ReceiveFunctionABI":
    state_mutability as StateMutability

Type called "FallbackFunctionABI":
    state_mutability as StateMutability
    payable as Boolean

Type called "StateVariableABI":
    name as String
    type as ABIType
    visibility as Visibility
    constant as Boolean
    immutable as Boolean

Type called "ContractMetadata":
    compiler as CompilerInfo
    language as String
    version as String
    settings as CompilerSettings
    sources as Dictionary[String, SourceInfo]
    bytecode as String
    deployed_bytecode as String
    source_map as String
    deployed_source_map as String

Type called "CompilerInfo":
    name as String
    version as String
    optimization_enabled as Boolean
    optimization_runs as Integer

Note: ABI Encoding and Decoding
Process called "encode_function_call" that takes function_abi as FunctionABI and arguments as List[Any] returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Validate argument count
    If length of arguments is not equal to length of function_abi["inputs"]:
        Throw create_abi_error with message as "Argument count mismatch"
    
    Note: Calculate function selector (first 4 bytes of keccak256 hash of signature)
    Let function_selector be calculate_function_selector with function_abi as function_abi
    
    Note: Encode arguments
    Let encoded_args be encode_parameters with parameters as function_abi["inputs"] and values as arguments
    
    Note: Combine selector and encoded arguments
    Let encoded_call be list containing
    For each byte in function_selector:
        Add byte to encoded_call
    For each byte in encoded_args:
        Add byte to encoded_call
    
    Return encoded_call

Process called "decode_function_result" that takes function_abi as FunctionABI and data as List[Integer] returns List[Any]:
    Note: Check if function has outputs
    If length of function_abi["outputs"] is equal to 0:
        Return list containing
    
    Note: Decode the return data
    Let decoded_values be decode_parameters with parameters as function_abi["outputs"] and data as data
    
    Return decoded_values

Process called "encode_parameters" that takes parameters as List[Parameter] and values as List[Any] returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Validate parameter count
    If length of parameters is not equal to length of values:
        Throw create_abi_error with message as "Parameter count mismatch"
    
    Let encoded_data be list containing
    Let dynamic_data be list containing
    Let dynamic_offset be calculate_static_size with parameters as parameters
    
    Note: First pass: encode static types and calculate dynamic offsets
    For i from 0 to (length of parameters minus 1):
        Let parameter be parameters at index i
        Let value be values at index i
        
        If is_dynamic_type with type as parameter["type"]:
            Note: Encode offset for dynamic type
            Let offset_bytes be encode_uint256 with value as dynamic_offset
            For each byte in offset_bytes:
                Add byte to encoded_data
            
            Note: Encode dynamic data
            Let encoded_dynamic be encode_single_parameter with parameter as parameter and value as value
            For each byte in encoded_dynamic:
                Add byte to dynamic_data
            
            Set dynamic_offset to dynamic_offset plus length of encoded_dynamic
        Otherwise:
            Note: Encode static type directly
            Let encoded_static be encode_single_parameter with parameter as parameter and value as value
            For each byte in encoded_static:
                Add byte to encoded_data
    
    Note: Append dynamic data
    For each byte in dynamic_data:
        Add byte to encoded_data
    
    Return encoded_data

Process called "decode_parameters" that takes parameters as List[Parameter] and data as List[Integer] returns List[Any]:
    Let decoded_values be list containing
    Let data_offset be 0
    
    For each parameter in parameters:
        Let decoded_result be decode_single_parameter with parameter as parameter and data as data and offset as data_offset
        Add decoded_result["value"] to decoded_values
        Set data_offset to decoded_result["new_offset"]
    
    Return decoded_values

Process called "encode_single_parameter" that takes parameter as Parameter and value as Any returns List[Integer]:
    Let abi_type be parameter["type"]
    
    Match abi_type["base_type"]:
        When UINT:
            Return encode_uint with size as abi_type["size_in_bytes"] and value as value
        
        When INT:
            Return encode_int with size as abi_type["size_in_bytes"] and value as value
        
        When ADDRESS:
            Return encode_address with value as value
        
        When BOOL:
            Return encode_bool with value as value
        
        When BYTES:
            If abi_type["is_dynamic"]:
                Return encode_dynamic_bytes with value as value
            Otherwise:
                Return encode_fixed_bytes with size as abi_type["size_in_bytes"] and value as value
        
        When STRING:
            Return encode_string with value as value
        
        When ARRAY:
            If abi_type["is_dynamic"]:
                Return encode_dynamic_array with element_type as abi_type["components"] at index 0 and value as value
            Otherwise:
                Return encode_fixed_array with element_type as abi_type["components"] at index 0 and size as abi_type["array_size"] and value as value
        
        When TUPLE:
            Return encode_tuple with components as abi_type["components"] and value as value
        
        Otherwise:
            Throw create_abi_error with message as "Unsupported type for encoding"

Process called "decode_single_parameter" that takes parameter as Parameter and data as List[Integer] and offset as Integer returns DecodingResult:
    Let abi_type be parameter["type"]
    
    Match abi_type["base_type"]:
        When UINT:
            Return decode_uint with size as abi_type["size_in_bytes"] and data as data and offset as offset
        
        When INT:
            Return decode_int with size as abi_type["size_in_bytes"] and data as data and offset as offset
        
        When ADDRESS:
            Return decode_address with data as data and offset as offset
        
        When BOOL:
            Return decode_bool with data as data and offset as offset
        
        When BYTES:
            If abi_type["is_dynamic"]:
                Return decode_dynamic_bytes with data as data and offset as offset
            Otherwise:
                Return decode_fixed_bytes with size as abi_type["size_in_bytes"] and data as data and offset as offset
        
        When STRING:
            Return decode_string with data as data and offset as offset
        
        When ARRAY:
            If abi_type["is_dynamic"]:
                Return decode_dynamic_array with element_type as abi_type["components"] at index 0 and data as data and offset as offset
            Otherwise:
                Return decode_fixed_array with element_type as abi_type["components"] at index 0 and size as abi_type["array_size"] and data as data and offset as offset
        
        When TUPLE:
            Return decode_tuple with components as abi_type["components"] and data as data and offset as offset
        
        Otherwise:
            Throw create_abi_error with message as "Unsupported type for decoding"

Type called "DecodingResult":
    value as Any
    new_offset as Integer

Note: Function Signature and Selector Calculation
Process called "calculate_function_selector" that takes function_abi as FunctionABI returns List[Integer]:
    Let signature be generate_function_signature with function_abi as function_abi
    Let signature_hash be keccak256_hash with data as signature
    
    Note: Return first 4 bytes
    Return signature_hash from index 0 to index 3

Process called "generate_function_signature" that takes function_abi as FunctionABI returns String:
    Let signature be function_abi["name"] with message "("
    
    For i from 0 to (length of function_abi["inputs"] minus 1):
        Let parameter be function_abi["inputs"] at index i
        Set signature to signature with message generate_type_string with type as parameter["type"]
        
        If i is less than (length of function_abi["inputs"] minus 1):
            Set signature to signature with message ","
    
    Set signature to signature with message ")"
    
    Return signature

Process called "generate_type_string" that takes type as ABIType returns String:
    Match type["base_type"]:
        When UINT:
            Return "uint" with message string from type["size_in_bytes"] times 8
        
        When INT:
            Return "int" with message string from type["size_in_bytes"] times 8
        
        When ADDRESS:
            Return "address"
        
        When BOOL:
            Return "bool"
        
        When BYTES:
            If type["is_dynamic"]:
                Return "bytes"
            Otherwise:
                Return "bytes" with message string from type["size_in_bytes"]
        
        When STRING:
            Return "string"
        
        When ARRAY:
            Let element_type_string be generate_type_string with type as type["components"] at index 0
            If type["is_dynamic"]:
                Return element_type_string with message "[]"
            Otherwise:
                Return element_type_string with message "[" with message string from type["array_size"] with message "]"
        
        When TUPLE:
            Let tuple_string be "("
            For i from 0 to (length of type["components"] minus 1):
                Let component_string be generate_type_string with type as type["components"] at index i
                Set tuple_string to tuple_string with message component_string
                
                If i is less than (length of type["components"] minus 1):
                    Set tuple_string to tuple_string with message ","
            
            Set tuple_string to tuple_string with message ")"
            Return tuple_string
        
        Otherwise:
            Return "unknown"

Note: Event Handling and Log Parsing
Process called "decode_event_log" that takes event_abi as EventABI and log_entry as LogEntry returns EventData:
    Note: Verify event signature
    If length of log_entry["topics"] is greater than 0:
        Let event_topic be log_entry["topics"] at index 0
        If event_topic is not equal to event_abi["topic_hash"]:
            Throw create_abi_error with message as "Event signature mismatch"
    
    Note: Separate indexed and non-indexed parameters
    Let indexed_params be list containing
    Let non_indexed_params be list containing
    
    For each param in event_abi["inputs"]:
        If param["indexed"]:
            Add param to indexed_params
        Otherwise:
            Add param to non_indexed_params
    
    Note: Decode indexed parameters from topics
    Let indexed_values be list containing
    For i from 0 to (length of indexed_params minus 1):
        Let topic_index be i plus 1  Note: Skip first topic (event signature)
        If topic_index is less than length of log_entry["topics"]:
            Let topic_data be log_entry["topics"] at index topic_index
            Let decoded_value be decode_single_parameter with parameter as indexed_params at index i and data as topic_data and offset as 0
            Add decoded_value["value"] to indexed_values
    
    Note: Decode non-indexed parameters from data
    Let non_indexed_values be decode_parameters with parameters as non_indexed_params and data as log_entry["data"]
    
    Note: Combine indexed and non-indexed values
    Let all_values be dictionary containing
    Let indexed_index be 0
    Let non_indexed_index be 0
    
    For each param in event_abi["inputs"]:
        If param["indexed"]:
            Set all_values[param["name"]] to indexed_values at index indexed_index
            Set indexed_index to indexed_index plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Set all_values[param["name"]] to non_indexed_values at index non_indexed_index
            Set non_indexed_index to non_indexed_index plus 1
    
    Return EventData with:
        event_name as event_abi["name"]
        values as all_values
        raw_log as log_entry

Type called "EventData":
    event_name as String
    values as Dictionary[String, Any]
    raw_log as LogEntry

Type called "LogEntry":
    address as String
    topics as List[String]
    data as List[Integer]
    block_number as Integer
    transaction_hash as String
    log_index as Integer

Note: Contract Interface Definition
Process called "create_contract_interface" that takes abi_json as String returns ContractInterface:
    Let parsed_abi be parse_abi_json with json_string as abi_json
    Let contract_abi be create_contract_abi_from_parsed with parsed_data as parsed_abi
    
    Let function_map be dictionary containing
    For each function in contract_abi["functions"]:
        Let selector be calculate_function_selector with function_abi as function
        Set function_map[selector] to function
    
    Let event_map be dictionary containing
    For each event in contract_abi["events"]:
        Set event_map[event["topic_hash"]] to event
    
    Return ContractInterface with:
        abi as contract_abi
        function_selectors as function_map
        event_signatures as event_map
        deployment_bytecode as contract_abi["metadata"]["bytecode"]
        runtime_bytecode as contract_abi["metadata"]["deployed_bytecode"]

Type called "ContractInterface":
    abi as ContractABI
    function_selectors as Dictionary[String, FunctionABI]
    event_signatures as Dictionary[String, EventABI]
    deployment_bytecode as String
    runtime_bytecode as String

Process called "prepare_contract_call" that takes interface as ContractInterface and function_name as String and arguments as List[Any] returns ContractCall:
    Note: Find function by name
    Let function_abi be find_function_by_name with interface as interface and name as function_name
    If function_abi is None:
        Throw create_abi_error with message as "Function not found: " with message function_name
    
    Note: Encode function call
    Let encoded_call be encode_function_call with function_abi as function_abi and arguments as arguments
    
    Note: Estimate gas
    Let gas_estimate be estimate_function_gas with function_abi as function_abi and arguments as arguments
    
    Return ContractCall with:
        function_name as function_name
        function_abi as function_abi
        encoded_data as encoded_call
        gas_estimate as gas_estimate
        arguments as arguments

Type called "ContractCall":
    function_name as String
    function_abi as FunctionABI
    encoded_data as List[Integer]
    gas_estimate as Integer
    arguments as List[Any]

Note: Standard Contract Interfaces
Process called "create_erc20_interface" returns ContractInterface:
    Let erc20_abi be ContractABI with:
        contract_name as "ERC20"
        contract_version as "1.0"
        functions as create_erc20_functions
        events as create_erc20_events
        errors as list containing
        constructor as create_erc20_constructor
        receive_function as None
        fallback_function as None
        state_variables as create_erc20_state_variables
        inheritance as list containing
        metadata as create_empty_metadata
    
    Return create_contract_interface_from_abi with abi as erc20_abi

Process called "create_erc20_functions" returns List[FunctionABI]:
    Let functions be list containing
    
    Note: name() function
    Let name_function be FunctionABI with:
        name as "name"
        function_type as FUNCTION
        inputs as list containing
        outputs as list containing create_string_parameter with name as ""
        state_mutability as VIEW
        payable as false
        constant as true
        pure as false
        view as true
        visibility as PUBLIC
        modifiers as list containing
        gas_estimate as 2000
        selector as calculate_selector_for_signature with signature as "name()"
        signature as "name()"
    Add name_function to functions
    
    Note: symbol() function
    Let symbol_function be FunctionABI with:
        name as "symbol"
        function_type as FUNCTION
        inputs as list containing
        outputs as list containing create_string_parameter with name as ""
        state_mutability as VIEW
        payable as false
        constant as true
        pure as false
        view as true
        visibility as PUBLIC
        modifiers as list containing
        gas_estimate as 2000
        selector as calculate_selector_for_signature with signature as "symbol()"
        signature as "symbol()"
    Add symbol_function to functions
    
    Note: decimals() function
    Let decimals_function be FunctionABI with:
        name as "decimals"
        function_type as FUNCTION
        inputs as list containing
        outputs as list containing create_uint8_parameter with name as ""
        state_mutability as VIEW
        payable as false
        constant as true
        pure as false
        view as true
        visibility as PUBLIC
        modifiers as list containing
        gas_estimate as 2000
        selector as calculate_selector_for_signature with signature as "decimals()"
        signature as "decimals()"
    Add decimals_function to functions
    
    Note: totalSupply() function
    Let total_supply_function be FunctionABI with:
        name as "totalSupply"
        function_type as FUNCTION
        inputs as list containing
        outputs as list containing create_uint256_parameter with name as ""
        state_mutability as VIEW
        payable as false
        constant as true
        pure as false
        view as true
        visibility as PUBLIC
        modifiers as list containing
        gas_estimate as 2000
        selector as calculate_selector_for_signature with signature as "totalSupply()"
        signature as "totalSupply()"
    Add total_supply_function to functions
    
    Note: balanceOf(address) function
    Let balance_of_function be FunctionABI with:
        name as "balanceOf"
        function_type as FUNCTION
        inputs as list containing create_address_parameter with name as "owner"
        outputs as list containing create_uint256_parameter with name as ""
        state_mutability as VIEW
        payable as false
        constant as true
        pure as false
        view as true
        visibility as PUBLIC
        modifiers as list containing
        gas_estimate as 2500
        selector as calculate_selector_for_signature with signature as "balanceOf(address)"
        signature as "balanceOf(address)"
    Add balance_of_function to functions
    
    Note: transfer(address,uint256) function
    Let transfer_function be FunctionABI with:
        name as "transfer"
        function_type as FUNCTION
        inputs as list containing create_address_parameter with name as "to", create_uint256_parameter with name as "amount"
        outputs as list containing create_bool_parameter with name as ""
        state_mutability as NONPAYABLE
        payable as false
        constant as false
        pure as false
        view as false
        visibility as PUBLIC
        modifiers as list containing
        gas_estimate as 25000
        selector as calculate_selector_for_signature with signature as "transfer(address,uint256)"
        signature as "transfer(address,uint256)"
    Add transfer_function to functions
    
    Note: approve(address,uint256) function
    Let approve_function be FunctionABI with:
        name as "approve"
        function_type as FUNCTION
        inputs as list containing create_address_parameter with name as "spender", create_uint256_parameter with name as "amount"
        outputs as list containing create_bool_parameter with name as ""
        state_mutability as NONPAYABLE
        payable as false
        constant as false
        pure as false
        view as false
        visibility as PUBLIC
        modifiers as list containing
        gas_estimate as 25000
        selector as calculate_selector_for_signature with signature as "approve(address,uint256)"
        signature as "approve(address,uint256)"
    Add approve_function to functions
    
    Return functions

Process called "create_erc20_events" returns List[EventABI]:
    Let events be list containing
    
    Note: Transfer event
    Let transfer_event be EventABI with:
        name as "Transfer"
        inputs as list containing create_indexed_address_parameter with name as "from", create_indexed_address_parameter with name as "to", create_uint256_parameter with name as "value"
        anonymous as false
        signature as "Transfer(address,address,uint256)"
        topic_hash as calculate_event_topic_hash with signature as "Transfer(address,address,uint256)"
    Add transfer_event to events
    
    Note: Approval event
    Let approval_event be EventABI with:
        name as "Approval"
        inputs as list containing create_indexed_address_parameter with name as "owner", create_indexed_address_parameter with name as "spender", create_uint256_parameter with name as "value"
        anonymous as false
        signature as "Approval(address,address,uint256)"
        topic_hash as calculate_event_topic_hash with signature as "Approval(address,address,uint256)"
    Add approval_event to events
    
    Return events

Note: Type Encoding and Decoding Primitives
Process called "encode_uint256" that takes value as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Encode as big-endian 32-byte integer
    Let bytes be list containing
    For i from 31 down to 0:
        Let byte_value be (value divided by (256 to the power of i)) modulo 256
        Add byte_value to bytes
    Return bytes

Process called "decode_uint256" that takes data as List[Integer] and offset as Integer returns DecodingResult:
    Note: Validate bounds
    If offset plus 32 is greater than length of data:
        Throw create_abi_error with message as "Insufficient data for uint256"
    
    Let value be 0
    For i from 0 to 31:
        Let byte_value be data at index (offset plus i)
        Set value to value plus (byte_value times (256 to the power of (31 minus i)))
    
    Return DecodingResult with:
        value as value
        new_offset as offset plus 32

Process called "encode_address" that takes value as String returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Address is 20 bytes, padded to 32 bytes
    Let address_bytes be hex_string_to_bytes with hex_string as value
    Let padded_bytes be list containing
    
    Note: Pad with 12 zero bytes at the beginning
    For i from 0 to 11:
        Add 0 to padded_bytes
    
    Note: Add address bytes
    For each byte in address_bytes:
        Add byte to padded_bytes
    
    Return padded_bytes

Process called "encode_string" that takes value as String returns List[Integer]:
    Let string_bytes be string_to_utf8_bytes with string as value
    Let length be length of string_bytes
    
    Note: Encode length first
    Let encoded_length be encode_uint256 with value as length
    
    Note: Encode string data with padding
    Let encoded_string be list containing
    For each byte in encoded_length:
        Add byte to encoded_string
    
    For each byte in string_bytes:
        Add byte to encoded_string
    
    Note: Pad to 32-byte boundary
    Let padding_needed be (32 minus (length modulo 32)) modulo 32
    For i from 0 to (padding_needed minus 1):
        Add 0 to encoded_string
    
    Return encoded_string

Process called "encode_dynamic_array" that takes element_type as ABIType and value as List[Any] returns List[Integer]:
    Let array_length be length of value
    
    Note: Encode array length
    Let encoded_length be encode_uint256 with value as array_length
    
    Note: Encode array elements
    Let encoded_elements be list containing
    For each element in value:
        Let element_param be Parameter with:
            name as ""
            type as element_type
            indexed as false
            internal_type as ""
            components as list containing
        
        Let encoded_element be encode_single_parameter with parameter as element_param and value as element
        For each byte in encoded_element:
            Add byte to encoded_elements
    
    Note: Combine length and elements
    Let result be list containing
    For each byte in encoded_length:
        Add byte to result
    For each byte in encoded_elements:
        Add byte to result
    
    Return result

Note: Gas Estimation
Process called "estimate_function_gas" that takes function_abi as FunctionABI and arguments as List[Any] returns Integer:
    Note: Base gas cost for function call
    Let base_gas be 21000
    
    Note: Additional gas for function execution
    Match function_abi["state_mutability"]:
        When VIEW:
            Set base_gas to base_gas plus 2000
        When PURE:
            Set base_gas to base_gas plus 1000
        When NONPAYABLE:
            Set base_gas to base_gas plus 5000
        When PAYABLE:
            Set base_gas to base_gas plus 5000
    
    Note: Gas for input data
    Let input_data_gas be calculate_input_data_gas with parameters as function_abi["inputs"] and values as arguments
    
    Note: Use stored estimate if available
    If function_abi["gas_estimate"] is greater than 0:
        Return function_abi["gas_estimate"] plus input_data_gas
    
    Return base_gas plus input_data_gas

Process called "calculate_input_data_gas" that takes parameters as List[Parameter] and values as List[Any] returns Integer:
    Let gas_cost be 0
    
    For i from 0 to (length of parameters minus 1):
        Let parameter be parameters at index i
        Let value be values at index i
        
        Note: 4 gas per byte for calldata
        Let encoded_size be estimate_encoded_size with parameter as parameter and value as value
        Set gas_cost to gas_cost plus (encoded_size times 4)
    
    Return gas_cost

Note: Utility Functions and Helpers
Process called "find_function_by_name" that takes interface as ContractInterface and name as String returns FunctionABI:
    For each function in interface["abi"]["functions"]:
        If function["name"] is equal to name:
            Return function
    
    Return None

Process called "calculate_selector_for_signature" that takes signature as String returns String:
    Let signature_hash be keccak256_hash with data as signature
    Return signature_hash from index 0 to index 3

Process called "calculate_event_topic_hash" that takes signature as String returns String:
    Return keccak256_hash with data as signature

Process called "hex_string_to_bytes" that takes hex_string as String returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Convert hex string to byte array
    Let bytes be list containing
    Let cleaned_hex be hex_string
    
    Note: Remove 0x prefix if present
    If cleaned_hex starts with "0x":
        Set cleaned_hex to cleaned_hex from index 2
    
    Note: Convert each pair of hex digits to byte
    For i from 0 to (length of cleaned_hex minus 1) by 2:
        Let hex_pair be cleaned_hex from index i to index (i plus 1)
        Let byte_value be hex_to_int with hex as hex_pair
        Add byte_value to bytes
    
    Return bytes

